issue.title: perf: Performance Optimization Phase 2 - Partytown, Self-hosted Fonts & Bundle Splitting #367
issue.body:
## üöÄ Performance Optimization Phase 2

This PR implements several critical performance optimizations identified in issue #367 to improve site performance and reduce bundle size.

### ‚úÖ Implemented Optimizations

#### 1. **Partytown Integration** 
- Moved Cloudflare Analytics to web worker using Partytown
- Prevents main thread blocking from third-party scripts
- Updated both BaseLayout and MobileOptimizedLayout

#### 2. **Self-Hosted Fonts**
- Eliminated Google Fonts CDN dependency
- Self-hosting Inter (400, 500, 600) and Playfair Display (400, 500, 600)
- Added font preloading for critical fonts
- Reduced 2+ network requests to external domains

#### 3. **Advanced Bundle Splitting**
- Enhanced Rollup configuration with feature-based chunks
- Separate chunks for: portfolio, contact, about, navigation features
- Split vendor bundles: react, framer-motion, icons, turnstile
- Better code organization for lazy loading

#### 4. **Component Optimization**
- Created Astro version of YouTubeEmbed component
- Prepared for future React ‚Üí Astro conversions

### üìä Expected Performance Impact

- **Reduced Main Thread Blocking**: Analytics run in web worker
- **Faster Font Loading**: No external font requests, preloaded critical fonts
- **Smaller Initial Bundle**: Better code splitting with feature-based chunks
- **Improved LCP**: Reduced render-blocking resources

### üîç Testing Checklist

- [ ] Fonts load correctly (no FOUT/FOIT)
- [ ] Analytics still track properly
- [ ] Bundle splitting works as expected
- [ ] No console errors
- [ ] Mobile performance improved
- [ ] Lighthouse score improvement

### üìà Metrics to Monitor

- Bundle size reduction (target: <350KB from current 508KB)
- Lighthouse score improvement (target: 90+ from current 60-70)
- LCP improvement
- Reduced network requests

### üîó Related Issues

Fixes part of #367 (Performance Optimization Phase 2)

### üìù Notes

- Font files are now committed to the repository (138KB total for all 6 font files)
- Partytown adds minimal overhead (~5KB) but significantly improves main thread performance
- Future optimizations can build on this foundation

### Next Steps (Not in this PR)

- Setup performance budget enforcement
- Add Lighthouse CI to GitHub Actions
- Create AnimateOnScroll Astro component
- Convert more React components to Astro where possible

pull_request.title: Add comprehensive localization support for multilingual documentation sites
pull_request.body:
This PR implements comprehensive localization support for Chloroplast, enabling creation of multilingual documentation sites without duplicating configuration or imposing language-centric assumptions.

## Key Features

### Configuration-Driven Localization
- **`defaultLocale`**: Specify the primary language of your content (can be any language, not just English)
- **`supportedLocales`**: Array of all supported languages
- **Customer-driven**: Users define their own primary language and additional translations

```yaml
# SiteConfig.yml
defaultLocale: es          # Spanish as primary language
supportedLocales:
  - es                     # Spanish (default)
  - en                     # English
  - fr                     # French
```

### Flexible Content Organization
Supports two naming conventions for translated content:

**Filename-based:**
```
content/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ guide.md              # Default language
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ guide.es.md          # Spanish translation
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ guide.fr.md          # French translation
```

**Directory-based:**
```
content/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ guide.md              # Default language
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ es/guide.md          # Spanish translation
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ fr/guide.md          # French translation
```

### Enhanced Content Model
Each `ContentNode` now includes:
- **`Locale`**: The language of the content
- **`Translations`**: Array of all available language versions
- Automatic detection and grouping of translations

### SEO-Friendly URL Structure
- **Default locale**: Clean URLs without locale prefix (`/docs/guide`)
- **Other locales**: Locale-prefixed URLs (`/es/docs/guide`, `/fr/docs/guide`)
- Proper canonical linking and `hreflang` attributes in sitemaps

### Template System Enhancements
New helper methods for Razor templates:
- **`LocaleHref(path, locale)`**: Generate locale-aware URLs
- **`GetLocalizedPageUrl(locale)`**: Get current page in different language
- **`GetCountryFlag(locale)`**: Country flag emojis (üá™üá∏, üá´üá∑, etc.)
- **`GetLocaleDisplayName(locale)`**: Native language names ("Espa√±ol", "Fran√ßais")

### Accessible Locale Picker Component
Complete footer component with:
- Dynamic generation based on configured languages
- Country flag emojis as requested
- Full keyboard navigation and ARIA attributes
- CSS and JavaScript for interactive functionality

### Intelligent Fallback System
- Falls back to default language when translation doesn't exist
- Template helpers for showing translation warnings
- Proper metadata linking to canonical versions

### Sitemap Integration
- All localized content included automatically
- Proper `hreflang` alternate links for SEO
- Search engine friendly structure

## Implementation Highlights

- **Zero breaking changes**: Existing sites work unchanged
- **90 passing tests**: Comprehensive test coverage including 22 new localization tests
- **Progressive enhancement**: Localization features are completely optional
- **Web standards compliant**: Follows internationalization best practices
- **Accessibility focused**: Full keyboard navigation and screen reader support

## Usage Example

After configuration, simply create translated files:

```
content/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ getting-started.md     # English (default)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ getting-started.es.md  # Spanish
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ getting-started.fr.md  # French
```

URLs automatically generated:
- `/getting-started` (English - no prefix)
- `/es/getting-started` (Spanish)
- `/fr/getting-started` (French)

Include the locale picker in templates:

This PR implements comprehensive localization support for Chloroplast, enabling creation of multilingual documentation sites without duplicating configuration or imposing language-centric assumptions.

## Key Features

### Configuration-Driven Localization
- **`defaultLocale`**: Specify the primary language of your content (can be any language, not just English)
- **`supportedLocales`**: Array of all supported languages
- **Customer-driven**: Users define their own primary language and additional translations

```yaml
# SiteConfig.yml
defaultLocale: es          # Spanish as primary language
supportedLocales:
  - es                     # Spanish (default)
  - en                     # English
  - fr                     # French
```

### Flexible Content Organization
Supports two naming conventions for translated content:

**Filename-based:**
```
content/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ guide.md              # Default language
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ guide.es.md          # Spanish translation
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ guide.fr.md          # French translation
```

**Directory-based:**
```
content/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ guide.md              # Default language
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ es/guide.md          # Spanish translation
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ fr/guide.md          # French translation
```

### Enhanced Content Model
Each `ContentNode` now includes:
- **`Locale`**: The language of the content
- **`Translations`**: Array of all available language versions
- Automatic detection and grouping of translations

### SEO-Friendly URL Structure
- **Default locale**: Clean URLs without locale prefix (`/docs/guide`)
- **Other locales**: Locale-prefixed URLs (`/es/docs/guide`, `/fr/docs/guide`)
- Proper canonical linking and `hreflang` attributes in sitemaps

### Template System Enhancements
New helper methods for Razor templates:
- **`LocaleHref(path, locale)`**: Generate locale-aware URLs
- **`GetLocalizedPageUrl(locale)`**: Get current page in different language
- **`GetCountryFlag(locale)`**: Country flag emojis (üá™üá∏, üá´üá∑, etc.)

Complete footer component with:
- Dynamic generation based on configured languages
- Country flag emojis as requested
- Full keyboard navigation and ARIA attributes
- CSS and JavaScript for interactive functionality

### Intelligent Fallback System
- Falls back to default language when translation doesn't exist
- Template helpers for showing translation warnings
- Proper metadata linking to canonical versions

### Sitemap Integration
- All localized content included automatically
- Proper `hreflang` alternate links for SEO
- Search engine friendly structure

- **Accessibility focused**: Full keyboard navigation and screen reader support
